# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MageInTheRuins1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah felt solid ground beneath her feet."
    new "Sarah felt solid ground beneath her feet."

    old "Her stuffy home, overflowing with books and old relics, had receded."
    new "Her stuffy home, overflowing with books and old relics, had receded."

    old "Sarah had barely looked around to take in her new surroundings, but before she did, she already knew she was somewhere else entirely."
    new "Sarah had barely looked around to take in her new surroundings, but before she did, she already knew she was somewhere else entirely."

    old "Everything about this place made that obvious."
    new "Everything about this place made that obvious."

    old "Thick, green vines ran along the floor and walls of the building she was standing in."
    new "Thick, green vines ran along the floor and walls of the building she was standing in."

    old "Light flittered in through gaps and cracks in the broken stone of what might once had been a house."
    new "Light flittered in through gaps and cracks in the broken stone of what might once had been a house."

    old "The air itself was heavy with humidity."
    new "The air itself was heavy with humidity."

    old "Drawing in her breath, Sarah could almost feel how fresh the air was here."
    new "Drawing in her breath, Sarah could almost feel how fresh the air was here."

    old "Lethram was a great city to live in, but it smelled about as one would expect when so many people lived so closely together."
    new "Lethram was a great city to live in, but it smelled about as one would expect when so many people lived so closely together."

    old "Next to her, Sarah saw Samayra."
    new "Next to her, Sarah saw Samayra."

    old "The girl seemed nervous, but also eager not to show it."
    new "The girl seemed nervous, but also eager not to show it."

    old "She was putting on a brave face."
    new "She was putting on a brave face."

    old "Sarah hoped she had not made a mistake in bringing the girl along."
    new "Sarah hoped she had not made a mistake in bringing the girl along."

    old "Ahead of her, Sarah saw either a doorway, or a wall with so much damage that it was essentially a doorway."
    new "Ahead of her, Sarah saw either a doorway, or a wall with so much damage that it was essentially a doorway."

    old "Walking forward, Sarah stepped out of the small house."
    new "Walking forward, Sarah stepped out of the small house."

    old "The few senses that had told her she was somewhere different, now screamed it."
    new "The few senses that had told her she was somewhere different, now screamed it."

    old "An overwhelming rush of sensations came over her as Sarah witnessed the world open up."
    new "An overwhelming rush of sensations came over her as Sarah witnessed the world open up."

    old "In front of her, a vast plaza, extended nearly as far as she could see."
    new "In front of her, a vast plaza, extended nearly as far as she could see."

    old "Like most things here, everything was made out of solid stone, as if the entire city had been carved out of a single block."
    new "Like most things here, everything was made out of solid stone, as if the entire city had been carved out of a single block."

    old "Though the vastness of it impressed her, Sarah also saw the ruin of this place."
    new "Though the vastness of it impressed her, Sarah also saw the ruin of this place."

    old "Everywhere she looked, she could see that nature had advanced on this place, reclaiming most of it."
    new "Everywhere she looked, she could see that nature had advanced on this place, reclaiming most of it."

    old "The stone, often broken or damaged. The colours, faded reminders and poor imitations of their brighter selves."
    new "The stone, often broken or damaged. The colours, faded reminders and poor imitations of their brighter selves."

    old "This place wasn't dying. It had died a long time ago."
    new "This place wasn't dying. It had died a long time ago."

    old "Above her, Sarah saw nothing but clear sky."
    new "Above her, Sarah saw nothing but clear sky."

    old "Travelling with Xan, she had seen a lot of strange places she had only ever read about."
    new "Travelling with Xan, she had seen a lot of strange places she had only ever read about."

    old "But he had never taken her here before."
    new "But he had never taken her here before."

    old "Beyond the edges of the city, Sarah saw nothing but massive trees, rising up so high she thought they might touch the clouds."
    new "Beyond the edges of the city, Sarah saw nothing but massive trees, rising up so high she thought they might touch the clouds."

    old "Not only was their size enormous, they were also plentiful."
    new "Not only was their size enormous, they were also plentiful."

    old "The thick jungle foliage was like a barrier around the city."
    new "The thick jungle foliage was like a barrier around the city."

    old "It's amazing. I never knew anything like this existed."
    new "It's amazing. I never knew anything like this existed."

    old "Sarah herself was impressed with this place, but she realized Samayra must have been even more so."
    new "Sarah herself was impressed with this place, but she realized Samayra must have been even more so."

    old "Even a regular forest must seem special to a girl born to the desert."
    new "Even a regular forest must seem special to a girl born to the desert."

    old "Sarah watched as Samayra began to walk across the plaza."
    new "Sarah watched as Samayra began to walk across the plaza."

    old "Don't go too far away from me."
    new "Don't go too far away from me."

    old "You think it's dangerous?"
    new "You think it's dangerous?"

    old "Until I know for sure it's safe, best to act like it's dangerous."
    new "Until I know for sure it's safe, best to act like it's dangerous."

    old "Samayra nodded, and remained close."
    new "Samayra nodded, and remained close."

    old "As Sarah continued to walk along the plaza, she saw other parts of the ancient city rise up in the distance."
    new "As Sarah continued to walk along the plaza, she saw other parts of the ancient city rise up in the distance."

    old "Great temples, spires and towering monuments."
    new "Great temples, spires and towering monuments."

    old "Some had entirely collapsed, but most still stood, ruined as they were."
    new "Some had entirely collapsed, but most still stood, ruined as they were."

    old "Varany. The first city, as it had been known."
    new "Varany. The first city, as it had been known."

    old "Here, if all of Xan's stories were to be believed, the first humans walked side-by-side with the Gods of the Pantheon."
    new "Here, if all of Xan's stories were to be believed, the first humans walked side-by-side with the Gods of the Pantheon."

    old "A marvel of miracle and magic, held together by the will of the Gods."
    new "A marvel of miracle and magic, held together by the will of the Gods."

    old "All brought low by the ambition of one woman."
    new "All brought low by the ambition of one woman."

    old "As her eyes roamed the now abandoned ruins, Sarah tried to imagine how this place must have looked at its peak."
    new "As her eyes roamed the now abandoned ruins, Sarah tried to imagine how this place must have looked at its peak."

    old "She couldn't."
    new "She couldn't."

    old "No matter how much she tried, she supposed that her imagination fell short."
    new "No matter how much she tried, she supposed that her imagination fell short."

    old "Slowly, a tall shadow creeped across the plaza."
    new "Slowly, a tall shadow creeped across the plaza."

    old "The light of day turned golden as the sun slowly crept down below the horizon."
    new "The light of day turned golden as the sun slowly crept down below the horizon."

    old "The city was enormous. She could probably get lost during the day, let alone at night."
    new "The city was enormous. She could probably get lost during the day, let alone at night."

    old "It would be better to make camp and set out early next morning."
    new "It would be better to make camp and set out early next morning."

    old "The girl turned about, busy exploring."
    new "The girl turned about, busy exploring."

    old "Let's make camp. It's going to be night time soon. I don't want us wandering this city at night."
    new "Let's make camp. It's going to be night time soon. I don't want us wandering this city at night."

    old "Swiftly they took off their backpacks and began making camp."
    new "Swiftly they took off their backpacks and began making camp."

    old "Sarah had assumed that Samayra might hold her back, but the girl proved to be the opposite."
    new "Sarah had assumed that Samayra might hold her back, but the girl proved to be the opposite."

    old "Moving swiftly, she unpacked her things and had begun to set up the basics of a camp."
    new "Moving swiftly, she unpacked her things and had begun to set up the basics of a camp."

    old "Sarah watched as Samayra waved her hand over a small pile of tinder and twigs that she had gathered."
    new "Sarah watched as Samayra waved her hand over a small pile of tinder and twigs that she had gathered."

    old "Blue flame flowed from the girl's hand, lighting the bonfire."
    new "Blue flame flowed from the girl's hand, lighting the bonfire."

    old "You're pretty good."
    new "You're pretty good."

    old "She saw Samayra smile, eager for the compliment."
    new "She saw Samayra smile, eager for the compliment."

    old "Not as good as you."
    new "Not as good as you."

    old "You'll get there. It took me years before I really felt comfortable using magic on my own."
    new "You'll get there. It took me years before I really felt comfortable using magic on my own."

    old "Metis just showed me the basics...I was hoping that you could..."
    new "Metis just showed me the basics...I was hoping that you could..."

    old "Of course I'm going to teach you."
    new "Of course I'm going to teach you."

    old "As much as I know, anyway."
    new "As much as I know, anyway."

    old "I'm sure you're a great teacher."
    new "I'm sure you're a great teacher."

    old "Sarah hoped she could be."
    new "Sarah hoped she could be."

    old "When they finished setting up camp, the sun dissapeared behind the massive trees and the city quickly went dark."
    new "When they finished setting up camp, the sun dissapeared behind the massive trees and the city quickly went dark."

    old "I'll take the first watch, you try to get some sleep."
    new "I'll take the first watch, you try to get some sleep."

    old "Samayra, already tired, didn't fight Sarah on it."
    new "Samayra, already tired, didn't fight Sarah on it."

    old "Sarah watched Samayra settle in for the night."
    new "Sarah watched Samayra settle in for the night."

    old "Sarah took off her backpack and began making camp."
    new "Sarah took off her backpack and began making camp."

    old "She gathered up some twigs and vines. They'd have to make do for a campfire."
    new "She gathered up some twigs and vines. They'd have to make do for a campfire."

    old "Sarah waved her hand across the tinder and blue flame rushed out from her hands."
    new "Sarah waved her hand across the tinder and blue flame rushed out from her hands."

    old "The magical fire lighted the bonfire."
    new "The magical fire lighted the bonfire."

    old "The sun settled behind the massive trees, quickly casting the city into darkness."
    new "The sun settled behind the massive trees, quickly casting the city into darkness."

    old "Before long, only the blue flames offered any light in the dark."
    new "Before long, only the blue flames offered any light in the dark."

    old "Sarah sat close to the fire."
    new "Sarah sat close to the fire."

    old "The city of Varany sat in the center of the jungle of Nephatim, on the southern-most border of the Mythran Empire."
    new "The city of Varany sat in the center of the jungle of Nephatim, on the southern-most border of the Mythran Empire."

    old "During the day, it could be sweltering hot."
    new "During the day, it could be sweltering hot."

    old "During the night, freezing cold."
    new "During the night, freezing cold."

    old "Up above, Sarah saw the stars, brighter than she ever remembered seeing them."
    new "Up above, Sarah saw the stars, brighter than she ever remembered seeing them."

    old "At night, there was a strange quiteness to the city."
    new "At night, there was a strange quiteness to the city."

    old "It took Sarah a moment to realize what it was."
    new "It took Sarah a moment to realize what it was."

    old "There were no animal noises."
    new "There were no animal noises."

    old "Not even the chirping of crickets. Only a dead silence."
    new "Not even the chirping of crickets. Only a dead silence."

    old "Nature had perhaps advanced on the city, but animals seemed to avoid it."
    new "Nature had perhaps advanced on the city, but animals seemed to avoid it."

    old "Perhaps they knew something instinctively, that humans by reason had forgotten."
    new "Perhaps they knew something instinctively, that humans by reason had forgotten."

    old "The crackling sound of the twigs being burned by the flame made Sarah feel at ease, despite this place."
    new "The crackling sound of the twigs being burned by the flame made Sarah feel at ease, despite this place."

    old "It reminded her of the hearth, back home."
    new "It reminded her of the hearth, back home."

    old "And further still, it reminded her of the large hearth in castle Reinmeer."
    new "And further still, it reminded her of the large hearth in castle Reinmeer."

    old "Sitting, playing near the fire, while her mother sat and watched."
    new "Sitting, playing near the fire, while her mother sat and watched."

    old "Sarah wondered why these memories plagued her now, when she had thought them banished from her mind."
    new "Sarah wondered why these memories plagued her now, when she had thought them banished from her mind."

    old "The light from the bonfire made the shadows dance on the walls of the plaza."
    new "The light from the bonfire made the shadows dance on the walls of the plaza."

    old "Sarah traced the shadows on the wall, the shapes, the forms, shifting..."
    new "Sarah traced the shadows on the wall, the shapes, the forms, shifting..."

    old "Changing..."
    new "Changing..."

    old "Sarah jumped to her feet."
    new "Sarah jumped to her feet."

    old "Wake up!"
    new "Wake up!"

    old "The girl woke and quickly jumped up to her feet."
    new "The girl woke and quickly jumped up to her feet."

    old "Blue fire wrapped itself around her hands. She was ready quick."
    new "Blue fire wrapped itself around her hands. She was ready quick."

    old "We're being attacked!"
    new "We're being attacked!"

    old "Movements in the dark."
    new "Movements in the dark."

    old "For a moment, she had imagined them only to be shadows, but now she saw their solid forms."
    new "For a moment, she had imagined them only to be shadows, but now she saw their solid forms."

    old "An arrow came flying out from the dark."
    new "An arrow came flying out from the dark."

    old "Sarah raised her hand, the flame caught the arrow, burning it so bright that turned to ashes."
    new "Sarah raised her hand, the flame caught the arrow, burning it so bright that turned to ashes."

    old "As the magical fires began to burn brighter, their light drove back the darkness further."
    new "As the magical fires began to burn brighter, their light drove back the darkness further."

    old "Illuminated, Sarah could make out the enemy."
    new "Illuminated, Sarah could make out the enemy."

    old "A group of orcs and goblins, armed with simple spears and crude knives, advanced across the plaza."
    new "A group of orcs and goblins, armed with simple spears and crude knives, advanced across the plaza."

    old "There seemed to be no strategy to their movement, but their numbers were more than enough for them to be dangerous."
    new "There seemed to be no strategy to their movement, but their numbers were more than enough for them to be dangerous."

    old "A single goblin rushed ahead of the pack."
    new "A single goblin rushed ahead of the pack."

    old "Sarah twisted her wrist, sending forth a pillar of fire which engulfed the small creature."
    new "Sarah twisted her wrist, sending forth a pillar of fire which engulfed the small creature."

    old "Only ashes remained."
    new "Only ashes remained."

    old "Off to the side of her, Sarah saw another goblin make a move for Samayra."
    new "Off to the side of her, Sarah saw another goblin make a move for Samayra."

    old "The girl, though less skilled, managed to produce enough magical fire to set the creature alight."
    new "The girl, though less skilled, managed to produce enough magical fire to set the creature alight."

    old "Samayra's flame burned less intensely, and instead, the goblin died screaming."
    new "Samayra's flame burned less intensely, and instead, the goblin died screaming."

    old "Sarah sighed a breath of relief, knowing that the girl could put up a fight."
    new "Sarah sighed a breath of relief, knowing that the girl could put up a fight."

    old "Still, she saw the panic on Samayra's face."
    new "Still, she saw the panic on Samayra's face."

    old "The other creatures of the advancing horde seemed to take notice."
    new "The other creatures of the advancing horde seemed to take notice."

    old "Instead of rushing forward, they began to encircle."
    new "Instead of rushing forward, they began to encircle."

    old "Seizing on the magical energies around her, Sarah began to weave a protective ward."
    new "Seizing on the magical energies around her, Sarah began to weave a protective ward."

    old "Another arrow flew out."
    new "Another arrow flew out."

    old "This time, it bounced off the magical barrier."
    new "This time, it bounced off the magical barrier."

    old "The barrier rippled, like a rock striking the surface of water."
    new "The barrier rippled, like a rock striking the surface of water."

    old "Sarah tried to see where the arrows were coming from."
    new "Sarah tried to see where the arrows were coming from."

    old "She spotted a small group of goblin archers on a hill, carrying bows."
    new "She spotted a small group of goblin archers on a hill, carrying bows."

    old "They were more organized than she had first assumed."
    new "They were more organized than she had first assumed."

    old "Sarah remembered Xan's lessons from years ago."
    new "Sarah remembered Xan's lessons from years ago."

    old "When they had travelled, for a brief moment, through the Hyral Mountains, home to the Orc Clans."
    new "When they had travelled, for a brief moment, through the Hyral Mountains, home to the Orc Clans."

    old "Though they had only gone there for a few hours, he had still taken the time to prepare her."
    new "Though they had only gone there for a few hours, he had still taken the time to prepare her."

    old "Teach her as much as he possibly could."
    new "Teach her as much as he possibly could."

    old "She had been bored at the time, but now she was grateful for his lessons."
    new "She had been bored at the time, but now she was grateful for his lessons."

    old "And one in particular came back to her."
    new "And one in particular came back to her."

    old "Goblin Poison."
    new "Goblin Poison."

    old "Orcs and goblins posed little danger to a skilled mage. Their weapons were crude and their tactics simple."
    new "Orcs and goblins posed little danger to a skilled mage. Their weapons were crude and their tactics simple."

    old "The only advantage, their physical strength and numbers, meant little to a mage."
    new "The only advantage, their physical strength and numbers, meant little to a mage."

    old "But there was one danger."
    new "But there was one danger."

    old "The goblins were known to brew a particular poison and apply it to their darts. A paralyzing agent."
    new "The goblins were known to brew a particular poison and apply it to their darts. A paralyzing agent."

    old "The miniscule darts of their blowguns were so small that the protective wards had trouble blocking them, unlike the heavier arrows."
    new "The miniscule darts of their blowguns were so small that the protective wards had trouble blocking them, unlike the heavier arrows."

    old "On the steps where the goblins were gathered, she saw them pull out a vial of the purple poison."
    new "On the steps where the goblins were gathered, she saw them pull out a vial of the purple poison."

    old "This was their strategy."
    new "This was their strategy."

    old "The orcs advanced to keep her distracted, while the goblins prepared the only real weapon they had."
    new "The orcs advanced to keep her distracted, while the goblins prepared the only real weapon they had."

    old "Attack the goblins"
    new "Attack the goblins"

    old "Keep defending against the orcs"
    new "Keep defending against the orcs"

    old "Whatever Xan had taught her was just theory."
    new "Whatever Xan had taught her was just theory."

    old "This was reality. And in the real world, an axe from an orc was a lot more pressing than a goblin."
    new "This was reality. And in the real world, an axe from an orc was a lot more pressing than a goblin."

